The bag you carry to work is so much more than just a thing to stuff your laptop in. It can serve as your home office, your plus-one at an event, an emotional support cushion for that deskside nap. But most importantly, your daily office tote needs to look good—no one wants to walk into a meeting with a backpack that makes you feel like an exhausted beetle or a briefcase that their dad carried to work (unless, of course, you’re Andy Sachs and have a vintage Coach messenger bag handy).
